The paper is about recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of social connections in recommendation systems suggests that it may also fall under social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also proposes a new framework for matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper's focus on local low-rank matrix approximation suggests that it may also fall under signal processing (cs.SI).
